cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CY, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the security implications of crowd-sourcing systems, which suggests a primary category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also analyzes the operational structure and effectiveness of these systems, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The study of the source of workers on these sites could also fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
